2026 Regular Session
SENATE RESOLUTION NO. 46
BY SENATOR CONNICK
SPECIAL DAY/WEEK/MONTH. Designates April as Landscape Architecture Month and
designates April 1 as Professional Landscape Architecture (PLA) Day at the Louisiana State
Capitol.
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To designate Wednesday, April 1, 2026, as Professional Landscape and Architecture Day
3 at the Louisiana State Capitol and to commend the members for the essential role
4 landscape architects play in shaping a resilient and enduring American landscape.
5 WHEREAS, the licensed practice of landscape architecture is ensuring that outdoor
6 environments, from therapeutic gardens and playgrounds, to complex stormwater and
7 transportation systems, are designed with technical rigor and ethical responsibility; and
8 WHEREAS, landscape architecture encompasses the analysis, planning, design, and
9 cultivation of the natural and built environment, in addition to shaping places that are
10 functional, durable, and accessible; and
11 WHEREAS, landscape architects are uniquely qualified to address challenges such
12 as flooding, coastal land loss, and urban heat through sustainable and resilient design
13 strategies; and
14 WHEREAS, landscape architects contribute to economic development, tourism, and
15 environmental protection, strengthening communities throughout urban, suburban, and rural
16 areas of the state by applying principles of science, technology, engineering, and
17 mathematics to the design of parks, streetscapes, campuses, transportation corridors, and
18 public spaces across Louisiana; and
