1 WHEREAS, as the United States approaches the "America 250" celebration, it is
2 recognized that landscape architects have historically shaped, and continue to steward the
3 American landscape, creating enduring places that embody democratic values and cultural
4 heritage, and advance opportunities for future generations; and
5 WHEREAS, the month of April is recognized as World Landscape Architecture
6 Month, celebrated and founded by the American Society of Landscape Architects (ASLA)
7 highlighting the impact of the profession nationwide and celebrated under the theme
8 Landscape Architecture in Action, recognizing the profession's tangible impact on urban,
9 suburban, and rural communities.
10 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Senate of the Legislature of Louisiana
11 does hereby designate Wednesday, April 1, 2026, as Professional Landscape and
12 Architecture Day at the Louisiana State Capitol and does commend the members for the
13 essential role landscape architects play in shaping a resilient and enduring American
14 landscape.
15 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of this Resolution be transmitted to the
16 president of the Louisiana Chapter of the American Society of Landscape Architects.
